Arab Investments Restarts Construction of London Tower, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-28T00:28:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/arab-investments-restarts-construction-of-london-tower-ft-says.html
Arab Investments Ltd., asset manager
for the 64-storey Pinnacle tower in the Bishopsgate section of
 London , has instructed global property group Brookfield to begin
the final phase of construction at the end of this month, the
Financial Times reported, citing Managing Director Khalid Affara.  The Pinnacle is to be completed by 2014 and will be
“delivered into a market where there will be a shortage of
high-quality  office space ,” Affara said, according to the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 